author: krochechka_xavrochechka
comment:
Thank you very much for supporting Ukraine in difficult times. that's why you help financially, etc.
War is a big wound for all of us.
I am 11 years old, on February 24, I woke up from some kind of familiarity...
I look at the time, and it's 10:42 a.m. I run to the kitchen and ask my mother:
Mom, why didn't you wake me up?
her words forever stuck in my soul,
we have a war...
That's all she told me.
and it is to this song that I:
rejoiced, cried, walked, rode, was sad, smiled, laughed, suffered, and was happy!
thank you for your music, it will always be in my memory..

author: ryder
comment: yesterday, at 23:57:04, I pressed play on this song (it was an accelerated version), so that when I hit 00:00 (my birthday), my favorite part would play (yes, I did the math so that the first few seconds of my 17 years started in the best possible way). unfortunately I didn't take a print to leave it as a memory, but I will never forget this moment, me listening to Another Love while having a mug of coffee with milk, waiting for my birthday, which, by the way, started in the best way possible. i have never been so happy in just one moment. all I have to say is, thank you, Tom. you are a great inspiration to me.
